MUTATION EVENTS AND OBSERVERS.  
Whenever events are added or removed from the DOM its structure changes. ïƒ  triggers a mutation event. 
Events that trigger when the DOM is changed. 
[DOMNodelnserted, DOMNodeRemoved, DOMSubtreeModified, DOMNodelnsertedlntoDocument]
When lots of mutation events fire this can make a page feel slow or unresponsive. 
Mutational events can trigger eventlisteners which modify other parts of the DOM triggering more mutational events. 
Mutational observers are designed to wait until a script has finished
